        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2584432525" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15981536951747903193">I’m a huge fan of Agatha Christie’s books! I really want to read all her books and I think I will read another 5 books written by her this month. Hopefully! <br/>About this book: It was a mix of suspense, mystery and in the end, romance. The romantic part was a surprise considering that I’m not used to read books written by this specific author that include romance. Usually it’s just the crime and the solution. But this one had two couples and the romance was present, especially in the end. But, to b</span>
  <span id="freeText15981536951747903193" style="display:none">I’m a huge fan of Agatha Christie’s books! I really want to read all her books and I think I will read another 5 books written by her this month. Hopefully! <br />About this book: It was a mix of suspense, mystery and in the end, romance. The romantic part was a surprise considering that I’m not used to read books written by this specific author that include romance. Usually it’s just the crime and the solution. But this one had two couples and the romance was present, especially in the end. But, to be honest, of course I’m not used with romance in Agatha’s books because I’ve read mostly books about Hercule Poirot. <br />Back to this book: I guessed who the “bad guy” was somewhere around the middle of the book. It was predictable, but I still liked the twists and turns this book kept throwing at me. 5 stars! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️</span>
  <a data-text-id="15981536951747903193" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
